PROCEEDS FROM ISSUANCES OF DEBT, NET OF REPAYMENTS. CASH USED IN INVESTING DECREASED $5.0 BILLION TO $18.8 BILLION, DUE MAINLY TO A $10.5 BILLION DECREASE IN CASH USED FOR NET INVESTMENT

